Irrara is believed to be derived from a local Aboriginal word. - Irrara Creek.

Irrara County, New South Wales is one of the 141 Cadastral divisions of New South Wales . It is located south of the border with Queensland , east of the Paroo River , and west of the Warrego River . It includes the localities of Yantabulla and Fords Bridge.
